\b Summary
\b0 \
When web design teams ramp up a website for users of assistive technology and\
other edge cases, the payoff happens at many levels. The website will likely be\
easier to find, be of a higher quality, be easier to maintain, last longer and work\
better for everyone - all of which contribute to a better return on the investment. Just\
like accessible ramps at building entrances, the virtual ramp built into websites\
benefits more than the intended audience.\
